I will call Barton,
discuss his moving his practice

14:59.167 --> 15:00.733
back with us.

15:00.768 --> 15:02.768
As for speaking engagements,
interviews--

15:02.804 --> 15:05.071
We can decide
on a case-by-case basis.

15:05.106 --> 15:06.772
As for seeing new patients--

15:06.808 --> 15:08.274
We both will,
with our new partners.

15:08.309 --> 15:10.209
I assume you approve
of Dr. Leveau.

15:10.244 --> 15:12.044
She has sterling
qualifications.

15:12.080 --> 15:15.147
Mmm, I would prefer someone
with more clinical experience,

15:15.183 --> 15:17.917
but as long as you don't mind
some hand-holding.

15:17.952 --> 15:19.552
She is very knowledgeable
about the work.

15:19.587 --> 15:21.787
Well, knowing is not the same
as doing.

15:21.823 --> 15:23.389
Whomever we hire,

15:23.424 --> 15:25.558
we will have to keep
a very close eye on them.

15:25.593 --> 15:28.227
So I would like to tighten
our oversight

15:28.262 --> 15:31.063
by having Lester install
recording equipment

15:31.099 --> 15:33.833
in the conference room
and all the exam rooms.

15:33.868 --> 15:36.569
Recording equipment?
To record?

15:36.604 --> 15:39.338
Everything.
Sessions with patients,

15:39.373 --> 15:41.307
conversations between
staff members.

15:41.342 --> 15:44.009
Why? I can't imagine
any new hire

15:44.045 --> 15:46.011
is going to stand
being listened in on.

15:46.047 --> 15:49.815
And yet if we had tape recorders
in this office two months ago,

15:49.851 --> 15:52.451
we wouldn't be staring down
the barrel at criminal charges.

15:52.487 --> 15:55.187
[knocking]

15:55.223 --> 15:57.857
Courier just delivered these
for you.

15:57.892 --> 15:59.658
We're in the middle
of a session, Betty.

15:59.694 --> 16:02.495
You asked me to get you
if any deliveries came for you.

16:02.530 --> 16:05.164
Remember?
So, here I am.

16:06.534 --> 16:08.801
Right. Well, do you know
who they're from?

16:08.836 --> 16:11.704
Was there a card?

16:11.739 --> 16:15.641
"Virginia, counting the hours
until I see you again.

16:15.676 --> 16:17.743
All my love, Dan."

16:20.414 --> 16:24.350
I am going to call Dr. Leveau,
make the official offer.

16:24.385 --> 16:26.018
All right, you can put those
in my office,

16:26.053 --> 16:27.620
and then I need you to pull
together a list

16:27.655 --> 16:29.822
of psychiatrists
for potential new partners.

16:29.857 --> 16:32.191
I need to start that interview
process as soon as possible.

16:32.226 --> 16:34.326
Or...

16:34.362 --> 16:37.062
you could show
a little appreciation

16:37.098 --> 16:38.564
every once in a while.

16:38.599 --> 16:40.533
Whatever it is
you're trying to say,

16:40.568 --> 16:42.801
why don't you just say it?

16:42.837 --> 16:45.538
Okay.
I've spent the past two months

16:45.573 --> 16:47.540
tap-dancing as fast as I can
trying to keep

16:47.575 --> 16:50.009
this business together
with spit and Scotch tape.

16:50.044 --> 16:53.746
And in all that time...
[scoffs]

16:53.781 --> 16:58.083
...I didn't hear so much
as a peep from you.

16:58.119 --> 16:59.718
You're right,
I should have called.

16:59.754 --> 17:01.520
I'm sorry.

17:01.556 --> 17:03.556
- Woulda, coulda, shoulda.
- What do you want me to say?

17:03.591 --> 17:05.558
Words are not
what I'm looking for.

17:05.593 --> 17:07.660
See, Helen is out-to-here
pregnant,

17:07.694 --> 17:10.496
which means
I got another mouth to feed.

17:10.531 --> 17:12.364
Now, I haven't had a raise

17:12.400 --> 17:14.066
since Truman
was in the White House.

17:14.101 --> 17:16.402
Which is a problem,
because in my household,

17:16.436 --> 17:19.070
I am Truman, as in,
the buck stops with me.

17:19.106 --> 17:22.208
As I am also the breadwinner
in my house.

17:22.242 --> 17:23.776
So, why don't we pick a time
next week

17:23.810 --> 17:24.944
to sit down and discuss it.

17:24.979 --> 17:26.744
Unfortunately, right now,

17:26.781 --> 17:29.048
uh, my plate is very full
with everything going on here.

17:29.083 --> 17:31.884
Or we can take care of this
right now.

17:31.919 --> 17:34.086
See,

17:34.121 --> 17:37.423
I have been working here
for ten years.

17:37.458 --> 17:41.560
And I know your handwriting
from a mile away.

17:41.596 --> 17:44.196
Now, I don't know why

17:44.232 --> 17:46.732
you're sending yourself flowers
from Dan,

17:46.767 --> 17:51.470
and... I'm not asking.

17:51.505 --> 17:56.308
What I am asking for
is a little bit of support.

17:58.946 --> 18:01.647
So I made a fearless
moral inventory

18:01.682 --> 18:04.583
of all the people that
did me wrong all these years,

18:04.619 --> 18:06.819
beginning with my mother.

18:06.854 --> 18:09.255
She called the cops on me
last year

18:09.290 --> 18:12.224
because I broke into her
and my stepdad's house

18:12.260 --> 18:13.959
when I knew
that they were at bingo.

18:13.995 --> 18:17.997
[chuckles]
That pissed her off royally.

18:18.032 --> 18:19.798
Irregardless, though,

18:19.834 --> 18:23.168
how does a mother call the cops
on her own flesh and blood?

18:23.204 --> 18:25.137
It's unnatural.

18:25.172 --> 18:27.172
Next person
is my asshole brother.

18:35.616 --> 18:37.283
Why are you in the dark?

18:37.318 --> 18:38.917
Atmosphere.
[chuckles]

18:38.953 --> 18:40.452
I mean, how many times
am I gonna get the chance

18:40.488 --> 18:42.021
to bug an office?

18:42.056 --> 18:43.822
This is as cloak and dagger
as it gets for me.

18:43.858 --> 18:46.692
- And it's all automatic?
- Yeah. Voice-activated.

18:46.727 --> 18:48.527
As soon as the mic picks up
people talking,

18:48.562 --> 18:52.097
the tape recorders in my office
start recording.

18:52.133 --> 18:54.366
- Great.
- Hey, hey.

18:54.402 --> 18:55.868
Can I try something
out on you?

18:55.903 --> 18:58.671
[exhales sharply]

18:58.706 --> 19:00.372
Linden.

19:00.408 --> 19:02.941
Lester Linden.

19:02.977 --> 19:05.010
I could pull it off, right?

19:05.046 --> 19:09.615
No.
Don't do that.

19:09.650 --> 19:12.651
Yeah, okay.

19:12.687 --> 19:14.219
[grunts]

19:16.223 --> 19:17.856
You think you're just going
to sit there

19:17.892 --> 19:20.359
waiting on me
to take you home?

19:20.394 --> 19:22.628
If you're here,
you're working.

19:22.663 --> 19:24.396
Help me with these chairs.

19:29.003 --> 19:30.869
And don't think I didn't see
the way you were looking

19:30.905 --> 19:33.072
at Kevin tonight.

19:33.107 --> 19:34.840
Hmm.

19:34.875 --> 19:36.975
If I had a penny
for every one of those looks,

19:37.011 --> 19:38.911
I'd be driving
a Cadillac.

19:38.946 --> 19:40.846
And what look is that?

19:40.881 --> 19:43.048
That look that says,
"This guy?

19:43.084 --> 19:45.217
"I got nothing in common
with this guy.

19:45.252 --> 19:47.653
"Well, why am I in the same room
with this guy?

19:47.688 --> 19:50.723
In fact, why am I here
with any of these people?"

19:50.758 --> 19:52.558
The thought has crossed
my mind.

19:52.593 --> 19:55.361
Now, I'm not saying
he entirely understood

19:55.396 --> 19:57.196
the point of the fourth step.

19:57.231 --> 20:00.499
Oh, that, uh, a fearless
moral inventory

20:00.534 --> 20:03.202
isn't simply a list of excuses
for why everyone else

20:03.237 --> 20:06.205
in the world is to blame
for your own poor choices?

20:06.240 --> 20:08.774
That's not an uncommon mistake,

20:08.809 --> 20:12.010
to-- to blame others first
before you look at yourself

20:12.046 --> 20:15.681
and the destruction you caused,
but he is trying.

20:15.716 --> 20:18.250
Which is more than I can say
for some of us

20:18.285 --> 20:21.086
who haven't even started
the first step.

20:21.122 --> 20:24.423
See, that's the problem
with this program of yours.

20:24.458 --> 20:27.059
The interminable steps.

20:27.094 --> 20:29.261
Belaboring everything.

20:29.296 --> 20:31.897
Change is a process,
not an event.

20:31.932 --> 20:34.733
[groans]
And there's the other problem.

20:34.769 --> 20:37.236
The endless slogans.

20:37.271 --> 20:41.273
With all the profundity
of a fortune cookie.

20:41.308 --> 20:45.611
Hmm. Well, I guess
you got it all wired.

20:45.646 --> 20:47.746
I didn't say "all wired."

20:50.584 --> 20:54.920
Although, a week ago,

20:54.955 --> 20:56.722
my business was in shambles.

20:56.757 --> 20:59.224
Now, it's up and running.

20:59.260 --> 21:02.161
Even begun to hire
new employees.

21:02.196 --> 21:05.731
And tonight,
I'm going to go see my wife,

21:05.766 --> 21:08.834
and hammer out
a custody arrangement.

21:08.869 --> 21:10.769
Ex-wife.

21:10.805 --> 21:12.337
For your information,
the divorce papers

21:12.373 --> 21:13.906
aren't even drafted yet.

21:13.941 --> 21:15.607
Soon-to-be-ex-wife.

21:15.643 --> 21:20.479
Point is... if you're looking
for a success story,

21:20.514 --> 21:22.247
it ain't Kevin.

21:22.283 --> 21:25.083
And where are you living
these days, Bill?

21:25.119 --> 21:27.119
'Cause I've been picking you up
and dropping you off

21:27.154 --> 21:29.822
at your office almost like
you're sleeping there,

21:29.857 --> 21:31.924
but that can't be true.

21:31.959 --> 21:34.726
I mean, for a success story
like you.

21:38.399 --> 21:40.799
My upstairs neighbor,
Phyllis,

21:40.835 --> 21:43.035
spends every winter
in Fort Lauderdale.

21:43.070 --> 21:45.437
Um, now if you're willing
to water the plants

21:45.473 --> 21:47.873
and feed the cat,

21:47.908 --> 21:50.275
I can get you settled
in there tonight.

21:50.311 --> 21:52.211
Well, as tempting
as that sounds.

21:52.246 --> 21:54.246
You got a better option?

22:04.325 --> 22:06.024
I thought maybe
we could sit down--

22:06.060 --> 22:09.728
listen, Libby, Libby, I-I talked
with Johnny this morning.

22:09.763 --> 22:11.330
He refuses to see me.

22:11.365 --> 22:13.232
He says his siblings
feel the same.

22:13.267 --> 22:14.967
Well, I can't vouch
for the baby,

22:15.002 --> 22:17.870
but yes, Johnny and Jenny
are furious with you.

22:17.905 --> 22:19.738
Well, perhaps they're taking
cues from their mother.

22:19.773 --> 22:21.507
Well, I don't know
what you've told them.

22:21.542 --> 22:23.208
I know you've poisoned
the neighbors against me.

22:23.244 --> 22:24.743
- The other parents--
- Are you blaming this on me?

22:24.778 --> 22:26.411
No, I'm not saying-- no.

22:26.447 --> 22:29.147
Lib, Libby.
Libby.

22:29.183 --> 22:32.117
[indistinct chatter]

22:35.523 --> 22:37.656
Another, please.
Two olives.

22:37.691 --> 22:40.659
[ <i>♪ jazz music playing ♪</i> ]

22:40.694 --> 22:45.631
<i>♪</i>

22:49.937 --> 22:53.338
Dr. Madden.

22:53.374 --> 22:56.108
Perhaps you don't remember me.
Virginia Johnson.

22:58.045 --> 22:59.444
May I join you?

22:59.480 --> 23:01.580
Actually, I'm waiting
for someone.

23:05.119 --> 23:06.952
This whole pretending-not-to-
know-who-I-am,

23:06.987 --> 23:09.454
it's on purpose,
I assume.

23:09.490 --> 23:11.223
It's against
ethical guidelines

23:11.258 --> 23:12.624
for me to acknowledge
a patient--

23:12.660 --> 23:14.293
- Former patient.
- Um, yes.

23:14.328 --> 23:17.596
In public.
So, yes, it is on purpose.

23:17.631 --> 23:19.865
Oh, first date?

23:19.900 --> 23:22.100
He's seated at the bar.
He's waiting for you.

23:22.136 --> 23:25.137
- Okay, thank you.
- Hi.

23:27.241 --> 23:31.276
- [clears throat]
- A blind first date.

23:31.312 --> 23:34.646
Dr. Madden,
I'm disappointed.

23:34.682 --> 23:37.916
The manager of a casino
doesn't play the slots.

23:37.952 --> 23:39.918
You're a therapist,
Dr. Madden,

23:39.954 --> 23:43.155
and yet here you are pumping
quarters into the machine,

23:43.190 --> 23:48.093
fingers crossed that you'll be
the one to hit the jackpot.

23:48.128 --> 23:50.295
Does your husband know

23:50.331 --> 23:52.931
that he's married to a woman
that doesn't believe in love?

23:52.967 --> 23:56.802
Oh, it turns out he's not much
of a romantic either.

23:56.837 --> 23:58.003
How late is she?

24:00.808 --> 24:03.609
15 minutes.

24:03.644 --> 24:05.978
Well, she could still
turn up.

24:06.013 --> 24:07.646
[scoffs]

24:07.681 --> 24:09.281
She's a Leo,

24:09.316 --> 24:13.251
so our chances weren't great
to begin with.

24:13.287 --> 24:16.154
That was a joke.

24:16.190 --> 24:18.290
[chuckles]

24:18.325 --> 24:20.626
You know,
it's fortuitous,

24:20.661 --> 24:23.095
running into you like this,
Dr. Madden.

24:23.130 --> 24:27.599
'Cause I think I may have
a business opportunity for you.

24:27.635 --> 24:30.302
[crickets chirping]

24:33.307 --> 24:36.074
Cab's on its way, so...

24:39.980 --> 24:43.115
I'm no longer living
in a hotel.

24:43.150 --> 24:46.885
Or staying in my office.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.887
An associate knew
of an apartment,

24:48.922 --> 24:52.224
so, uh,
now you can rest assured,

24:52.259 --> 24:55.627
if the children change their
minds and agree to see me,

24:55.663 --> 24:57.963
they have a place to stay.

24:57.998 --> 25:01.066
There's even a pull-out sofa,
I'm told.

25:06.940 --> 25:09.941
You want something?
[clears throat]

25:15.082 --> 25:16.648
Oh, I'm going to AA meetings
now.

25:16.684 --> 25:17.883
Did I tell you that?

25:19.887 --> 25:22.354
Uh, it's-- it's court-ordered.

25:25.259 --> 25:28.760
Uh, people seem to find the,
uh,

25:28.796 --> 25:33.065
the exercises therapeutic.

25:33.100 --> 25:37.536
There's one they call, uh,
the "inventory."

25:37.571 --> 25:40.572
You make a list
of all the people you've hurt,

25:43.277 --> 25:44.976
all the people
you've disappointed.

25:51.952 --> 25:54.386
I know there's no one I've hurt
as much as you, Libby.

25:56.957 --> 25:58.957
And I'm sorry.

26:05.132 --> 26:06.765
For everything I've done.

26:12.639 --> 26:13.638
[sniffs]

26:16.143 --> 26:17.309
Let's call it even.

26:23.817 --> 26:26.651
Do you really think
all those years

26:26.687 --> 26:29.454
that I just sat here
making lunches

26:29.490 --> 26:31.757
and vacuuming the carpets

26:31.792 --> 26:34.893
while you were working late?

26:34.928 --> 26:35.894
[scoffs]

26:35.929 --> 26:39.898
First, there was Robert.

26:39.933 --> 26:42.267
You remember Robert.

26:42.302 --> 26:45.103
Coral's brother?

26:45.139 --> 26:48.240
The first time, we didn't even
make it to the bedroom.

26:48.275 --> 26:51.643
He took me right there
on the kitchen floor.

26:51.678 --> 26:55.113
Anybody walking by
could have seen us.

26:55.149 --> 26:57.482
But I wanted him so badly,

26:57.518 --> 26:59.484
it didn't even matter.

27:02.189 --> 27:05.624
Then, there was Paul.

27:08.362 --> 27:11.196
There is not a room
in this house

27:11.231 --> 27:14.132
where Paul and I
didn't make love.

27:14.168 --> 27:15.700
Certainly,
there was this room.

27:15.736 --> 27:18.203
[ <i>♪ soft music ♪</i> ]

27:18.238 --> 27:20.839
Every inch of it, really.

27:20.874 --> 27:23.475
There was the rug.

27:23.510 --> 27:25.043
Up against the bar.

27:26.980 --> 27:28.413
On this sofa.

27:30.818 --> 27:33.952
Paul wanted to marry me,

27:33.987 --> 27:36.988
take me away.

27:37.024 --> 27:38.156
The kids too.

27:40.027 --> 27:41.259
And I should have gone.

27:46.867 --> 27:48.333
I should have gone.

27:53.006 --> 27:57.976
So, if you want
to feel sorry for someone,

27:58.011 --> 28:01.713
I would suggest feeling sorry
for yourself.

28:01.748 --> 28:06.585
<i>♪</i>

28:06.620 --> 28:08.086
[car honks]

28:10.057 --> 28:13.558
That would be your taxi.

28:13.594 --> 28:16.862
I'm flattered by the offer,
but I'm-- I'm very happy

28:16.897 --> 28:18.496
with my practice.

28:18.532 --> 28:19.764
Really?

28:20.968 --> 28:22.734
Really?

28:22.769 --> 28:24.903
You don't get tired
of the same people,

28:24.938 --> 28:28.673
the same problems,
year after year?

28:28.709 --> 28:30.408
With the protocols
that we've developed,

28:30.444 --> 28:35.413
we can transform patient's lives
in a matter of weeks.

28:35.449 --> 28:37.883
You do know that there are
psychologists in St. Louis

28:37.918 --> 28:40.385
far more qualified than I am
for this job.

28:40.420 --> 28:44.122
You're a Yale undergrad
with a PhD from Columbia.

28:44.157 --> 28:45.924
Plus, in my case,

28:45.959 --> 28:50.729
everything you told me
as a patient was spot-on.

28:50.764 --> 28:53.398
I was full of excuses,
like you said.

28:53.433 --> 28:55.634
Living in denial
of the consequences

28:55.669 --> 28:58.703
of my own behavior.

28:58.739 --> 29:01.640
You told me what
I needed to hear.

29:01.675 --> 29:05.744
And as a result, you've sorted
out your life, have you?

29:05.779 --> 29:07.779
[chuckles]

29:13.153 --> 29:15.654
Please think about it.

29:15.689 --> 29:19.591
If I have a change of heart,
I will call you.

29:19.626 --> 29:21.893
Well...

29:21.929 --> 29:23.461
...good luck
with the slots.

29:29.703 --> 29:31.703
[exasperated sigh]

29:36.810 --> 29:38.410
Sorry to bother,

29:38.445 --> 29:40.812
but I was wondering
if you had any tips

29:40.847 --> 29:43.281
for my first day.

29:43.317 --> 29:44.950
You are the expert,
obviously,

29:44.985 --> 29:49.287
when it comes
to working with Bill, so...

29:49.323 --> 29:52.857
Well, my first tip would be
to call him Dr. Masters.

29:52.893 --> 29:55.293
[chuckles]
But other than that,

29:55.329 --> 29:56.761
you're his partner now.

29:56.797 --> 29:59.531
You'll find your own way
of working together.

29:59.566 --> 30:02.334
Also, I know that
you are interviewing

30:02.369 --> 30:04.102
for another staff psychiatrist,

30:04.137 --> 30:07.973
and I-I have a friend,
a family friend,

30:08.008 --> 30:10.642
who I think would be perfect
for the role.

30:10.677 --> 30:12.277
Perfect?

30:12.312 --> 30:14.212
That's a strong word.

30:14.247 --> 30:17.449
He's young,
but he is very accomplished.

30:17.484 --> 30:20.385
Oh, well, I already
have a long list of candidates

30:20.420 --> 30:21.820
to see today, but, uh,

30:21.855 --> 30:23.555
I suppose we can try
to squeeze him in.

30:23.590 --> 30:25.123
Why don't you give Betty
his information?

30:25.158 --> 30:26.424
Of course.

30:29.262 --> 30:30.261
[knocking]

30:33.266 --> 30:34.799
How's the bachelor pad?

30:34.835 --> 30:37.235
[exhales deeply]
I feel if I moved to Mars,

30:37.270 --> 30:39.004
you would still stalk me.

30:39.039 --> 30:41.573
One of the perks of driving
with me to the first meeting

30:41.608 --> 30:43.908
of the day is
you get to make the coffee.

30:43.944 --> 30:46.378
I'm not going.

30:46.413 --> 30:48.480
So I'll make the coffee,

30:48.515 --> 30:49.981
but that means you setting up
the chairs.

30:50.017 --> 30:52.250
I just told you,
I'm not going.

30:52.285 --> 30:55.153
Fine. If you're not going,
I'm not going.

30:55.188 --> 30:57.489
Wh-- what-- what do you want
from me, exactly?

30:57.524 --> 30:59.491
Because let me be
perfectly clear,

30:59.526 --> 31:02.494
I will not, uh, uh,
take inventory,

31:02.529 --> 31:05.430
or-- or make amends,
or say anything, ever,

31:05.465 --> 31:07.599
in any AA meeting.

31:07.634 --> 31:10.668
All I want
is to be left alone.

31:10.704 --> 31:12.837
[cat meows]

31:12.873 --> 31:15.106
I can wait.

31:15.142 --> 31:17.609
