to observe your own behavior,

48:41.921 --> 48:44.922
your own shortcomings.

48:47.093 --> 48:48.926
For that matter,

48:48.961 --> 48:52.229
what do you really know
about me?

48:52.264 --> 48:54.665
What I've had
to overcome in my life.

48:54.700 --> 48:58.635
The enormous sacrifices
that I have had to make

48:58.671 --> 49:01.138
to get on all
of those magazine covers.

49:04.777 --> 49:06.910
I am very good at my job

49:06.946 --> 49:08.779
because I don't judge.

49:10.883 --> 49:15.285
But given your... limitations,

49:15.321 --> 49:17.187
I think it's probably best
that we take your name

49:17.223 --> 49:20.023
out of consideration
for the position at the clinic.

49:20.059 --> 49:22.192
Wouldn't you agree?

49:22.228 --> 49:25.195
[ <i>♪ soft music ♪</i> ]

49:25.231 --> 49:26.830
<i>♪</i>

49:26.866 --> 49:28.298
[door slams]

49:28.334 --> 49:30.200
I hope you're not gonna make
a habit of this,

49:30.236 --> 49:31.702
stopping by unannounced.

49:31.737 --> 49:34.938
Well, no, no, no.
But I-I--

49:34.974 --> 49:36.707
Oh, I feel like

49:36.742 --> 49:38.509
things were left unsettled

49:38.544 --> 49:42.312
after we spoke last night.

49:42.348 --> 49:45.315
I don't feel unsettled
at all.

49:45.351 --> 49:48.051
Except by your clothes.

49:48.087 --> 49:50.554
What are you wearing?

49:50.589 --> 49:51.922
I didn't sleep a wink.

49:54.493 --> 49:55.826
I can see that.

50:00.266 --> 50:02.866
I'll admit what you told me
last night,

50:02.902 --> 50:07.070
it's, uh...
[exhales sharply]

50:07.106 --> 50:09.106
...it's very painful.

50:12.411 --> 50:13.710
[ <i>♪ soft music ♪</i> ]

50:13.746 --> 50:16.480
But I realize now...

50:16.515 --> 50:20.884
it is much better
that you found some pleasure

50:20.920 --> 50:24.488
somewhere,

50:24.523 --> 50:27.491
even if it wasn't
with me.

50:27.526 --> 50:31.061
[sighs]

50:31.096 --> 50:32.629
We were married, Bill.

50:34.700 --> 50:38.335
We should have found
our pleasure together.

50:38.370 --> 50:39.436
I know.

50:41.440 --> 50:43.540
It's just...

50:43.576 --> 50:45.309
there's so much that I...

50:47.479 --> 50:48.812
missed out on.

50:51.617 --> 50:54.618
An entire world out there.

50:56.622 --> 50:57.955
You're not dead.

50:57.990 --> 51:00.591
[chuckles]

51:00.626 --> 51:03.627
No...

51:03.662 --> 51:06.530
just 40.

51:06.565 --> 51:11.568
<i>♪</i>

51:17.009 --> 51:19.676
[dishes clatter]

51:21.513 --> 51:23.580
Honey, are you hungry?

51:23.616 --> 51:25.082
I was thinking
of making some eggs.

51:25.117 --> 51:27.217
I already ate.

51:27.253 --> 51:29.419
Well, then why don't I make
some French toast?

51:29.455 --> 51:33.323
That way, it can be dessert
for you and dinner for me.

51:33.359 --> 51:35.459
I'm not staying here tonight.
I'm moving in with Dad.

51:35.494 --> 51:36.960
Oh, Tessie, please.

51:36.996 --> 51:39.763
Can we not do this tonight?

51:39.798 --> 51:41.431
You don't have to do anything.

51:41.467 --> 51:43.333
But I have to take care
of myself.

51:46.005 --> 51:48.772
No, no, no.
Honey, wait.

51:48.807 --> 51:50.941
I understand that you're upset
with me,

51:50.976 --> 51:53.277
but... I took your advice.

51:53.312 --> 51:55.512
I saw a psychiatrist.

51:55.547 --> 51:57.648
- You did?
- Yes.

51:57.683 --> 51:58.782
What did he say?

51:58.817 --> 52:01.518
He said,
for the most part,

52:01.553 --> 52:04.955
that... people are doing
the best that they can.

52:04.990 --> 52:06.256
And that's really all
they can do.

52:06.292 --> 52:08.258
That is what I'm doing.

52:08.294 --> 52:10.027
So if that
is not good enough...

52:10.062 --> 52:12.462
It isn't.

52:12.498 --> 52:14.498
It isn't. I'm sorry.

52:23.475 --> 52:25.442
[sighs]

52:25.477 --> 52:28.945
Virginia?

52:28.981 --> 52:30.947
Libby.

52:30.983 --> 52:32.182
Welcome home.

52:34.186 --> 52:36.186
Coffee, please.

52:38.991 --> 52:41.058
Here you are.

52:41.093 --> 52:43.727
Great minds think alike.
[chuckles]

52:43.762 --> 52:48.465
I've actually been meaning
to call you to thank you for--

52:48.500 --> 52:50.567
for helping my dad
with the baby while I was away.

52:50.602 --> 52:53.637
Oh, that. I remembered that Lisa
liked to be held

52:53.672 --> 52:56.173
stomach-down when she was
a baby, so I tried that.

52:56.208 --> 52:59.910
Well, you were a saint
to do it.

53:02.948 --> 53:05.082
I've actually been meaning
to call you too.

53:05.117 --> 53:08.251
To congratulate you.

53:08.287 --> 53:11.221
You are married now?

53:11.256 --> 53:15.559
Yes, uh, it happened
very quickly.

53:15.594 --> 53:17.427
But you're happy?

53:17.463 --> 53:20.864
Very.
We both are.

53:20.899 --> 53:22.899
Good for you.

53:27.239 --> 53:30.440
[sighs] I really don't
know what to say, Libby.

53:30.476 --> 53:32.242
Other than, um...

53:34.713 --> 53:38.215
other than I'm sorry.

53:38.250 --> 53:41.918
I'm sorry about Bill.

53:41.954 --> 53:44.955
[chuckles]
Yes, well...

53:49.762 --> 53:53.630
I keep thinking
about that pact that we made.

53:53.665 --> 53:56.233
Do you remember that?

53:56.268 --> 53:59.102
I thought we were so clever,
what we'd come up with.

53:59.138 --> 54:02.439
Seemed...
foolproof.

54:02.474 --> 54:04.808
We only made
one tiny mistake,

54:04.843 --> 54:07.444
and we left out Bill,

54:07.479 --> 54:11.882
the one person
who could derail everything.

54:11.917 --> 54:15.652
I've also been thinking...

54:15.687 --> 54:20.157
if you and I had met
somewhere else, um,

54:20.192 --> 54:21.625
on an airplane

54:21.660 --> 54:25.962
or in a diner,

54:25.998 --> 54:27.998
would we still
have been friends?

54:33.172 --> 54:36.173
I'm sure we would have.

54:39.178 --> 54:41.611
I suppose we'll never know.
[chuckles]

54:41.647 --> 54:43.513
The only thing we ever really
had in common was Bill,

54:43.549 --> 54:44.781
and now, not even that.

54:44.817 --> 54:49.453
Oh, I'm not so sure
that matters.

54:49.488 --> 54:53.423
So we are friends?

54:53.459 --> 54:57.661
Of course we're friends,
Libby.

54:57.696 --> 55:00.163
I'm glad.

55:00.199 --> 55:01.965
Uh, what are you doing here?

55:02.000 --> 55:05.669
Me?
Oh, um, I'm going to work.

55:08.974 --> 55:11.775
[phone rings]

55:11.810 --> 55:13.009
Mrs. Masters?

55:13.045 --> 55:14.845
Uh, I thought
our next appointment

55:14.880 --> 55:16.213
wasn't until Tuesday.

55:16.248 --> 55:18.148
I'm not here
for an appointment.

55:18.183 --> 55:20.617
I am here for a job.

55:20.652 --> 55:22.619
I can't afford to have
an attorney whose office looks

55:22.654 --> 55:24.020
like it's been hit
by a hurricane.

55:24.056 --> 55:26.022
[chuckles]
You need a secretary.

55:26.058 --> 55:27.991
Someone to keep you organized.

55:28.026 --> 55:30.994
- I can start right away.
- [phone ringing]

55:31.029 --> 55:32.729
[laughing]

55:47.513 --> 55:50.013
We're three blocks
from the office.

55:50.048 --> 55:51.748
Nobody's gonna see us.

55:51.783 --> 55:53.984
Just wait, uh, a few minutes
after I'm gone.

55:54.019 --> 55:57.354
I just don't want to come in
too close together.

55:57.389 --> 56:00.824
Wish me luck on my first day.

56:00.859 --> 56:02.158
Good luck, baby.

56:02.194 --> 56:03.360
Hey, you'll be great.

56:08.100 --> 56:10.667
Dr. Dreessen,
I'm so glad this worked out.

56:10.702 --> 56:13.069
And I'm glad you looked
beyond all those fancy degrees

56:13.105 --> 56:15.438
- and chose me.
- Ah, well, like you said,

56:15.474 --> 56:18.375
